{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry consists of several lipoproteins mainly from Mycobacterium species, collectively known as the LppX/LprAFG family. Proteins in this entry include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>LprG ([swissprot:P0A5I8]) from Mycobacterium tuberculosis: an immunogenic 27kDa membrane-associated lipoprotein [[cite:PUB00020730]]. Expression of the LprG protein is essential for the growth of M. tuberculosis in immunocompetent mice [[cite:PUB00020731]]. Purification of LprG showed that it inhibits MHC-II antigen processing in primary human macrophages, providing a mechanism to avoid the host MHC-II-restricted CD4+ T cell response which is considered essential for control of M. tuberculosis infection [[cite:PUB00020732]].</li>\r\n\r\n<li>LppX: a lipoprotein required for the translocation of complex lipids to the outer membrane of Mycobacterium tuberculosis. Its structure consists of a U-shaped Î²-half-barrel with a large hydrophobic cavity [[cite:PUB00039808]].</li>\r\n\r\n<li>LprF: a membrane lipoprotein involved in the kdp signal transduction pathway, thought to be the primary response to osmotic stress [[cite:PUB00020734]].</li>\r\n<li>lprA: a lipoprotein agonist of TLR2 that regulates innate immunity and APC function [[cite:PUB00076900]].</li>\r\n</ul>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4zra", "name" "CRYSTAL STRUCTURE OF MYCOBACTERIUM TUBERCULOSIS LPRG BINDING TO TRIACYLGLYCERIDE"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR029046", "name" "Lipoprotein localisation LolA/LolB/LppX", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"cdd" {"cd16334" "family includes lipoproteins LppX, LprA, LprF and LprG from Mycobacterium tuberculosis"}, "pfam" {"PF07161" "LppX_LprAFG lipoprotein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "LppX/LprAFG lipoprotein family", "short" "LppX/LprAFG"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 6, "domain_